content:
CRM Analytics for Financial Services gives financial advisors a comprehensive customer intelligence solution based on the CRM Analytics platform. It includes Einstein Discovery, which lets you create automated AI models on any dataset without writing code.

Analytics for Wealth Management is a comprehensive analytics solution that applies the power of CRM Analytics to all significant data and KPIs from the Financial Services Cloud. Unique collections of dashboards provide insights for business growth.

Predict Client Churn Risk allows advisors to intelligently predict customer churn, while Predict Likelihood to Add Assets predicts the likelihood of adding assets to accounts. Einstein Discovery for Insurance Analytics gives predictions on the likelihood of policy renewals.

Insurance Claims and Policy Analytics enables claim handlers and producers to effectively manage their tasks, claims, quotes, and policies. Wealth Starter Analytics gets advisors quickly started with its My Book of Business dashboard. Analytics for Mortgage drives increased mortgage sales by prioritizing customer leads and applications.

To deploy CRM Analytics for Financial Services, follow the steps in sequence:
1. Enable Tableau CRM in your Salesforce org.
2. Assign CRM Analytics for Financial Services Administrator Permissions.
3. Grant Permission to the Analytics Integration User.
4. Assign CRM Analytics for Financial Services User Permissions.
5. Get Your Data Ready to Create CRM Analytics for Financial Services Apps.
6. Set Field-Level Security to Enable Creation of CRM Analytics for Financial Services Apps.
7. Create and Share CRM Analytics for Financial Services Apps.

Embed dashboards in Lightning Pages, schedule the data sync and dataflow, and delete records from Analytics for Insurance Datasets as necessary. Revenue Management gives financial advisors access to analytics that provide a comprehensive view of their business performance.
title: Deploying CRM Analytics for Financial Services
